 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🏦 Banking Intent Classification — Lab 2\n",
    "**Unsloth + QLoRA fine-tuning on Gemma-2-9B**\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook runs the full pipeline via the `scripts/` and shell scripts.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Project structure (per lab requirements)\n",
    "```\n",
    "Lab2/\n",
    "├── configs/              ← training & inference YAML configs\n",
    "├── outputs/              ← checkpoints & trained adapter\n",
    "├── sample_data/          ← train.csv, test.csv, id2label.csv\n",
    "├── scripts/              ← Python scripts (preprocess / train / inference)\n",
    "├── requirements.txt\n",
    "├── train.sh              ← calls scripts/preprocess_data.py + scripts/train.py\n",
    "├── inference.sh          ← calls scripts/inference.py\n",
    "├── upload.sh             ← pushes model to HuggingFace Hub\n",
    "└── banking_intent_model/ ← LoRA adapter (final output)\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📦 Section 0 — Setup & Dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Check environment\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "print(f\"Python : {sys.version}\")\n",
    "print(f\"CWD    : {os.getcwd()}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Verify key files exist\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "required_files = [\n",
    "    \"requirements.txt\",\n",
    "    \"scripts/preprocess_data.py\",\n",
    "    \"scripts/train.py\",\n",
    "    \"scripts/inference.py\",\n",
    "    \"configs/train.yaml\",\n",
    "    \"configs/inference.yaml\",\n",
    "    \"train.sh\",\n",
    "    \"inference.sh\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "missing = []\n",
    "for f in required_files:\n",
    "    if not Path(f).exists():\n",
    "        missing.append(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "if missing:\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n⚠️  Missing files:\")\n",
    "    for m in missing:\n",
    "        print(f\"   - {m}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"\\n✅ All required files present.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "import subprocess\n",
    "\n",
    "def run(cmd: str, desc: str = \"\"):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Run a shell command and print output.\"\"\"\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  ▶  {desc or cmd}\")\n",
    "    print('='*60)\n",
    "    result = subprocess.run(cmd, shell=True, capture_output=False)\n",
    "    if result.returncode != 0:\n",
    "        raise RuntimeError(f\"Command failed with exit code {result.returncode}\")\n",
    "    return result"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install / verify core packages\n",
    "# Unsloth + dependencies (run once; ignore if already installed)\n",
    "!pip install unsloth --quiet 2>/dev/null || print(\"Unsloth already installed or pip unavailable\")\n",
    "\n",
    "!pip install transformers==4.56.2 trl==0.22.2 peft datasets huggingface_hub \
",
    "    --quiet 2>/dev/null\n",
    "\n",
    "# Verify GPU\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "    gpu = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0)\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n✅ GPU: {gpu.name}  |  {round(gpu.total_memory/1024**3, 1)} GB\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"\\n⚠️  No GPU detected — training will be slow or fail.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📂 Section 1 — Download & Prepare Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Loads `mteb/banking77` from HuggingFace, saves `train.csv`, `test.csv`, and\n",
    "the full `id2label.csv` mapping (77 intents) into `sample_data/`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from datasets import load_dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create dirs\n",
    "os.makedirs(\"sample_data\", exist_ok=True)\n",
    "os.makedirs(\"configs\",   exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Load banking77 dataset ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "dataset = load_dataset(\"mteb/banking77\")\n",
    "\n",
    "train_df = dataset['train'].to_pandas()\n",
    "test_df  = dataset['test'].to_pandas()\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Save raw CSVs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "train_df.to_csv(\"sample_data/train.csv\", index=False)\n",
    "test_df.to_csv(\"sample_data/test.csv\",   index=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Build full id2label (all 77 intents) ───────────────────────────────────\n",
    "id2label = dict(zip(train_df['label'].astype(str), train_df['label_text']))\n",
    "mapping_df = pd.DataFrame(list(id2label.items()), columns=['label', 'label_text'])\n",
    "mapping_df.to_csv(\"sample_data/id2label.csv\", index=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✅ Train samples : {len(train_df)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"✅ Test  samples : {len(test_df)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"✅ Intent labels : {len(id2label)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nSample intents:\\n  {list(id2label.values())[:8]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Preview sample data ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "train_df.head(3)[['text', 'label', 'label_text']]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ⚙️ Section 2 — Preprocess Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Runs `scripts/preprocess_data.py` via `python` subprocess.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Parameters:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Param | Default | Description |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| `--data_dir` | `sample_data` | Folder chứa train.csv / test.csv |\n",
    "| `--output_dir` | `sample_data/processed` | Folder lưu kết quả đã xử lý |\n",
    "| `--model_name` | `unsloth/llama-3-8b-bnb-4bit` | Model tokenizer (chỉ dùng để tokenize) |\n",
    "| `--max_length` | `128` | Max sequence length |\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Note:** Preprocessing tokenizes data để train, tạo HuggingFace Dataset định dạng.\n",
    "   Nếu không cần preprocessing riêng (dùng trực tiếp train.py), bỏ qua cell này."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Preprocessing parameters ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "#  ↓ Thay đổi các giá trị tại đây nếu cần  ↓\n",
    "\n",
    "PREPROCESS_DATA_DIR   = \"sample_data\"                                    # input folder\n",
    "PREPROCESS_OUTPUT_DIR = \"sample_data/processed\"                         # output folder\n",
    "PREPROCESS_MODEL_NAME = \"unsloth/llama-3-8b-bnb-4bit\"                   # tokenizer model\n",
    "PREPROCESS_MAX_LEN    = 128                                              # max sequence length\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build the command\n",
    "preprocess_cmd = (\n",
    "    f\"python scripts/preprocess_data.py \"\n",
    "    f\"--data_dir {PREPROCESS_DATA_DIR} \"\n",
    "    f\"--output_dir {PREPROCESS_OUTPUT_DIR} \"\n",
    "    f\"--model_name {PREPROCESS_MODEL_NAME} \"\n",
    "    f\"--max_length {PREPROCESS_MAX_LEN}\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Command:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  {preprocess_cmd}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run\n",
    "run(preprocess_cmd, \"Preprocessing data\")\n",
    "print(\"\\n✅ Preprocessing done!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🚀 Section 3 — Training\n",
    "\n",
    "Runs `scripts/train.py` via `python` subprocess.\n",
    "Loads config từ `configs/train.yaml`, format data theo Alpaca template.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Parameters:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Param | Default | Description |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| `--config` | `configs/train.yaml` | File cấu hình training |\n",
    "| `--data_dir` | `sample_data` | Folder chứa train.csv & id2label.csv |\n",
    "| `--output_dir` | `outputs` | Folder lưu checkpoint |\n",
    "| `--id2label_path` | `auto` | File mapping (mặc định: `{data_dir}/id2label.csv`) |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Config in `configs/train.yaml` you can change:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Key | Default | Description |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| `model.name` | `unsloth/gemma-2-9b-bnb-4bit` | Base model |\n",
    "| `lora.r` | `16` | LoRA rank |\n",
    "| `training.num_train_epochs` | `3` | Số epoch |\n",
    "| `training.per_device_train_batch_size` | `2` | Batch size |\n",
    "| `training.learning_rate` | `2e-4` | Learning rate |\n",
    "| `training.gradient_accumulation_steps` | `4` | Gradient accumulation |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Training parameters ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "#  ↓ Thay đổi các giá trị tại đây nếu cần  ↓\n",
    "\n",
    "TRAIN_CONFIG        = \"configs/train.yaml\"       # config YAML file\n",
    "TRAIN_DATA_DIR      = \"sample_data\"             # folder with train.csv + id2label.csv\n",
    "TRAIN_OUTPUT_DIR    = \"outputs\"                 # output checkpoint folder\n",
    "# TRAIN_ID2LABEL     = None                      # set path explicitly, or None = auto\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build command\n",
    "train_cmd = f\"python scripts/train.py --config {TRAIN_CONFIG} --data_dir {TRAIN_DATA_DIR} --output_dir {TRAIN_OUTPUT_DIR}\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Uncomment & fill if using custom id2label path:\n",
    "# train_cmd += f\" --id2label_path {TRAIN_ID2LABEL}\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Command:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  {train_cmd}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nStarting training (this may take 30–120 min depending on GPU)...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "run(train_cmd, \"Fine-tuning Banking Intent Model\")\n",
    "print(\"\\n✅ Training done!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 💾 Section 4 — Save Model\n",
    "\n",
    "The LoRA adapter is already saved by `train.py` inside `outputs/`.\n",
    "This cell copies / reorganises it into `banking_intent_model/` and\n",
    "verifies all required files are present."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import shutil\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "MODEL_SRC  = Path(\"outputs\") / \"banking_intent_model\"\n",
    "MODEL_DEST = Path(\"banking_intent_model\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if MODEL_DEST.exists():\n",
    "    print(f\"⚠️  {MODEL_DEST} already exists — skipping copy.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    shutil.copytree(MODEL_SRC, MODEL_DEST)\n",
    "    print(f\"✅ Copied adapter to {MODEL_DEST}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nModel files:\")\n",
    "for f in sorted(MODEL_DEST.iterdir()):\n",
    "    size_mb = round(f.stat().st_size / 1024**2, 1)\n",
    "    print(f\"  {str(f):<45} {size_mb:>8} MB\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🔍 Section 5 — Inference & Evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "Runs `scripts/inference.py` via `python` subprocess.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Parameters:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Flag | Description |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| `--model_path` | Thư mục model (default: `banking_intent_model`) |\n",
    "| `--input_text` | Một câu duy nhất cần phân loại |\n",
    "| `--input_file` | File `.txt` chứa nhiều câu (mỗi dòng = 1 câu) |\n",
    "| `--output_file` | Lưu kết quả JSON |\n",
    "| `--evaluate` | Tính accuracy trên test set |\n",
    "| `--show_samples` | Hiển thị mẫu dự đoán kèm nhãn thực tế |\n",
    "| `--num_show_samples` | Số mẫu hiển thị (mặc định: 10) |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Choose the mode below by commenting / uncommenting the command.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import subprocess, sys\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Base inference command ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "INFER_MODEL_PATH = \"banking_intent_model\"\n",
    "base_cmd = f\"python scripts/inference.py --model_path {INFER_MODEL_PATH}\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── [MODE 1] Single query ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Predict intent for one sentence.\n",
    "inference_cmd = base_cmd + ' --input_text \"I lost my credit card, what do I do?\"'\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── [MODE 2] Interactive (uncomment to use) ──────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# inference_cmd = base_cmd  # no --input_text → interactive mode\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── [MODE 3] Batch from .txt file (uncomment to use) ────────────────────────\n",
    "# Create a queries.txt file first, then uncomment:\n",
    "# inference_cmd = base_cmd + ' --input_file queries.txt --output_file results.json'\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── [MODE 4] Evaluate accuracy on test set (uncomment to use) ───────────────\n",
    "# inference_cmd = base_cmd + ' --evaluate'\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── [MODE 5] Show sample predictions (uncomment to use) ────────────────────\n",
    "# inference_cmd = base_cmd + ' --show_samples --num_show_samples 15'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run the selected command\n",
    "print(\"Command:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  {inference_cmd}\")\n",
    "run(inference_cmd, \"Running inference\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ☁️ Section 6 — Push to HuggingFace Hub\n",
    "\n",
    "Runs `upload.sh` (or `push_to_hf.sh` in the model folder) via subprocess.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Parameters:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Param | Default | Description |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| `HF_TOKEN` | *(set below)* | HuggingFace write token |\n",
    "| `REPO_ID` | *(set below)* | Target repo, e.g. `yourname/banking-intent-gemma2-unsloth` |\n",
    "\n",
    "**⚠️ Replace HF_TOKEN and REPO_ID before running!**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n",
    "# ║  ⚠️  EDIT THESE BEFORE RUNNING!                              ║\n",
    "# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n",
    "HF_TOKEN = \"hf_YOUR_TOKEN_HERE\"                       # ← replace\n",
    "REPO_ID  = \"your-username/banking-intent-gemma2-unsloth\"  # ← replace\n",
    "\n",
    "if \"YOUR_TOKEN\" in HF_TOKEN:\n",
    "    raise ValueError(\n",
    "        \"⚠️  Please set your real HF_TOKEN in the cell above!\\n\"\n",
    "        \"   Get it at: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "os.environ[\"HF_TOKEN\"] = HF_TOKEN\n",
    "\n",
    "upload_cmd = (\n",
    "    f'python -c \"'\n",
    "    import os; from huggingface_hub import HfApi\n",
    "    api = HfApi()\n",
    "    api.create_repo(repo_id=\\\"{REPO_ID}\\\", repo_type=\\\"model\\\", private=False, exist_ok=True, token=os.getenv(\\\"HF_TOKEN\\\"))\n",
    "    api.upload_folder(\n",
    "        folder_path=\\\"banking_intent_model\\\",\n",
    "        repo_id=\\\"{REPO_ID}\\\",\n",
    "        repo_type=\\\"model\\\",\n",
    "        token=os.getenv(\\\"HF_TOKEN\\\"),\n",
    "        commit_message=\\\"Upload banking intent LoRA adapter (Gemma-2-9B)\\\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    print(f\\\"Upload thành công: https://huggingface.co/{REPO_ID}\\\")\n",
    "    '\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Uploading to:\", REPO_ID)\n",
    "run(upload_cmd, \"Uploading model to HuggingFace Hub\")"
   ]
  },
  {
